cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.NE 

The paper presents a novel approach for human activity recognition using deep neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The approach also involves the use of convolutional auto-encoders for unsupervised feature learning, which is related to computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the challenges of recognizing human activities from sensor data, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper proposes a new method for predicting sets of ongoing activity elements, which is related to neural networks (cs.NE).
